-- ── amplemarket → business-finance ──────────────────────────
('Amplemarket', 'amplemarket', 'All-in-one AI sales platform — Duo AI copilot, intent signals, multichannel outreach, and deliverability optimization in one workflow.', 'Amplemarket is an all-in-one AI sales platform that combines lead intelligence, intent-signal detection, multichannel outreach automation, and email deliverability optimization in a single workflow. The product''s distinguishing thesis is consolidation: most sales orgs cobble together Apollo (data) + Outreach (sequencing) + Smartlead (deliverability) + a separate intent-signal vendor — Amplemarket replaces all four. Duo AI Sales Copilot surfaces daily signals and research, drafts personalized outreach, and runs multichannel sequences across email / LinkedIn / voice notes / calls; lead intelligence pulls intent data from 40+ sources (job changes, competitor reviews, Slack communities, website visits); deliverability optimization includes a Domain Health Center, email warmup, and spam testing claimed to boost open rates 50%; Searcher and data enrichment cut bounce rates 50% with a B2B database. Used by Deel, Cabify, Ceros, and HPE. Recognized as a Gartner Cool Vendor for Generative AI for Sales. Amplemarket positions against Apollo (database-first), Outreach + Salesloft (sequencing incumbents), ZoomInfo (data-only), 11x and AiSDR (AI-only SDR plays), and Reply.io (similar all-in-one positioning).', 'https://amplemarket.com', 'paid', '[]'::jsonb, 'intermediate', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Duo AI Sales Copilot — daily signals + multichannel sequence automation","Lead intelligence + intent signals from 40+ sources","Multichannel sequences (email + LinkedIn + voice notes + calls)","Domain Health Center + email warmup + spam testing","Deliverability optimization (50% open rate boost claimed)","B2B contact database with enrichment","Searcher with 50% bounce rate reduction","CRM auto-sync with Salesforce / HubSpot / Outreach / Salesloft","Intent data covering job changes, competitor reviews, Slack communities","Personalization at scale across all channels"}', '{"Salesforce","HubSpot","Outreach","Salesloft","LinkedIn Sales Navigator","Apollo","Slack","Zapier","Make"}', true, '{"Mid-market and enterprise sales teams consolidating multiple point tools","Outbound SDR ops needing intent signals + sequencing + deliverability in one stack","Sales orgs already on Salesforce or HubSpot wanting deeper AI than native","Teams that have burnt domains on cheap cold-email tools and need real deliverability"}', '{"Solo founders and 1-2 person sales teams (overkill for low call volume)","Volume-first cold-email shops where Smartlead / Instantly are cheaper","Teams wanting only a contact database without sequencing (Apollo cheaper)","Buyers needing transparent public pricing before sales conversation"}', 'The most credible all-in-one AI sales platform consolidation play in 2026 — Amplemarket bundles what mid-market teams typically buy as Apollo + Outreach + Smartlead + an intent-data vendor. The Duo AI copilot and 40+-source intent intelligence are genuinely differentiated, and customer roster (Deel, HPE, Cabify) is enterprise-credible. It''s weaker than Apollo on raw database breadth, weaker than Outreach on entrenched sequence-builder install base, and the no-public-pricing demo-led motion is friction. Pick Amplemarket when you''re consolidating off 3+ sales tools; skip if you only need one piece (use the specialist).', now()),

-- ── sanebox → productivity ──────────────────────────────────
('SaneBox', 'sanebox', 'AI email triage — auto-sorts inbox by relevance, kills noise with BlackHole, snoozes low-priority mail across all email clients.', 'SaneBox is an AI-powered email triage service that learns what matters in your inbox and automatically sorts incoming messages into priority folders without requiring you to switch email clients. The product attaches to any IMAP / Exchange account (Gmail, Outlook, Apple Mail, Yahoo, FastMail, AOL, Microsoft Exchange, ActiveSync) so you keep your existing app. Core features: SaneLater auto-sorts non-priority email into a separate folder; BlackHole permanently removes unwanted senders; Snooze hides messages until a chosen time; Reminder alerts you to unreturned emails or self-set follow-ups; Daily Digest summarizes low-priority mail in one email; Sane Folders organize by sender or topic; Reply Tracking flags conversations that need follow-up. SaneBox claims users spend 3-4 hours less per week managing email. Positions against Superhuman (faster client UX, $30/mo, Gmail/Outlook only), Hey (opinionated email reinvention), Inbox Zero (open-source SaneLater alternative), Spike (chat-style inbox), Mimestream (Apple Mail-native Gmail client), and bolt-on AI summarization tools (Shortwave, Notion Mail).', 'https://www.sanebox.com', 'paid', '[]'::jsonb, 'beginner', false, '{"web","mobile"}', '{"AI email triage with relevance learning","SaneLater — auto-sort non-priority email into separate folder","BlackHole — permanently remove unwanted senders","Snooze — temporarily hide emails until specified times","Reminder — alerts on unreturned email or self-set follow-ups","Daily Digest — single summary email of low-priority mail","Sane Folders — automated sorting by sender or topic","Reply Tracking — flag conversations awaiting response","Works with any IMAP / Exchange account (no client switch)","Mobile + desktop transparent — works in your existing email app"}', '{"Gmail","Outlook","Apple Mail","Yahoo Mail","FastMail","AOL","Microsoft Exchange","ActiveSync","iOS Mail","Android Mail","IMAP"}', true, '{"Heavy email users (300+ messages/day) who don''t want to switch from Gmail / Outlook","People with multiple email accounts on different providers (works across all)","Solo professionals consultants who can''t justify Superhuman''s $30/mo","Privacy-conscious users wanting AI triage without rebuilding the inbox UX"}', '{"Users who want a faster email client UX (Superhuman is purpose-built for that)","Teams wanting collaborative inbox / shared mail (Hey / Front fit better)","People comfortable with Gmail filters + folders done manually","Buyers wanting AI compose / reply drafting (use Shortwave or Notion Mail)"}', 'The cleanest no-client-switch AI email triage tool for heavy email users — SaneBox attaches to any IMAP account and starts sorting in hours without forcing you off Gmail or Outlook. The 3-4 hours/week saved claim is conservative for actual high-volume users. It''s weaker than Superhuman on inbox UX speed (different category), weaker than Hey on opinionated email reinvention, and the homepage''s missing public tier $ is mild friction. Pick SaneBox when you have inbox overload but don''t want a new email app; skip if you''re willing to switch clients for Superhuman-grade speed.', now()),

-- ── soona → image-generation ────────────────────────────────
('soona', 'soona', 'AI ecommerce content platform — live virtual product shoots, AI editing, and on-brand templates for Shopify and Amazon brands.', 'soona is an ecommerce content platform that combines live virtual product photography and video shoots with AI editing tools and an asset-management workflow. The product''s differentiator vs traditional product photographers (typical $5K–$10K per shoot, multi-week turnaround) is on-demand live booking — brands attend remote shoots in real time via virtual studios, with model + stylist marketplace access for talent — paired with AI editing that handles background replacement, retouching, and platform-optimized resizing. Studio Pass at $149/booking gives non-members access to a single shoot; per-asset pricing at $39/photo and $93/video covers ongoing production with free editing. UGC (user-generated content) creator marketplace delivers authentic content fast. Brand-ready templates auto-format for Shopify, Amazon, and ad-platform requirements. 24-72 hour turnaround on most assets. Soona claims ~66% cost reduction and 5x faster delivery vs traditional product photography. Positions against PhotoAI and HeadshotPro (AI-only photo generators, no human shoots), Canva (design tool, no production), ShootProof (gallery management, no production), and traditional product photographers (slower + 3-5x more expensive).', 'https://soona.co', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Studio Pass","price":"$149 per booking","features":["Single live virtual studio shoot","Non-member access","Same-day attendance","Editing add-on available"]},{"plan":"Per-Asset","price":"$39/photo, $93/video","features":["Free editing included","Platform-optimized output (Shopify, Amazon, ads)","24-72 hour turnaround","Volume discounts available"]},{"plan":"Enterprise","price":"Contact sales","features":["Custom pricing for high-volume brands","Dedicated account manager","Bulk asset workflows","Brand template library"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', false, '{"web"}', '{"Live virtual product photography studios","Live virtual product video shoots","AI background replacement and retouching","Model and stylist marketplace","UGC creator marketplace","Brand-ready templates (Shopify / Amazon / ads)","24-72 hour turnaround","Per-asset pricing with free editing","Asset management and library","Platform-specific output optimization"}', '{"Shopify","Amazon","Etsy","Canva"}', true, '{"DTC ecommerce brands needing fast, professional product photography at scale","Shopify and Amazon sellers replacing $5K-$10K traditional photographer engagements","Marketing teams running paid ads needing platform-optimized creative","Brands launching new SKUs needing 24-72 hour turnaround"}', '{"Single-product hobbyist sellers (per-asset pricing adds up)","Brands needing on-location lifestyle shoots (soona is studio-based)","Pure AI-generated imagery seekers (PhotoAI / HeadshotPro cheaper)","Buyers wanting unlimited monthly subscriptions (soona is per-asset / per-shoot)"}', 'The default ecommerce content production platform for DTC brands in 2026 — soona''s live virtual studios + AI editing + per-asset pricing collapse traditional product photography''s $5K–$10K + multi-week timeline into $39/photo and 24-72 hours. The model marketplace and brand-ready templates are genuinely useful for ad-creative iteration. It''s weaker than pure AI generators (PhotoAI / HeadshotPro) on cost-per-image for non-photo-realistic needs, weaker than traditional photographers on lifestyle / on-location work, and the per-asset pricing surprises brands accustomed to flat monthly subscriptions. Pick soona when you''re a Shopify or Amazon seller scaling SKUs; skip for hobbyist / one-off shoots.', now()),

-- ── corecruit → business-finance ────────────────────────────
('CoRecruit', 'corecruit', 'AI assistant for recruitment agencies — botless interview transcription, automated ATS updates, and AI-generated candidate submittals.', 'CoRecruit is an AI assistant built specifically for recruitment agencies (not in-house corporate recruiting) that captures interview audio and video, generates transcriptions and notes, automatically updates ATS systems in real time, and produces branded candidate submittals with embedded video snippets. The Botless AI Notetaker captures interviews across Zoom, Microsoft Teams, Google Meet, mobile calls, and in-person meetings without showing a meeting bot — important for agency contexts where candidates may not consent to a visible recording assistant. AI-generated submittals create professional candidate summaries in seconds; multi-language transcription provides speaker attribution and instant summaries from custom templates; integrated VoIP lets recruiters call clients and candidates from inside the ATS via browser extension or mobile app. SOC 2 Type II + GDPR compliant. Customer-reported metrics: 50% faster time-to-fill, 90% faster submittals, 8 hours/recruiter/week saved, 4.9/5 G2 average. Positions against BrightHire and Metaview (interview intelligence for in-house teams), HireVue and Modern Hire (assessment-first), Hireflix (async video interviewing), and Eightfold (broader talent-intelligence platform).', 'https://www.corecruit.ai', 'paid', '[]'::jsonb, 'intermediate', true, '{"web","mobile","plugin"}', '{"Botless AI Notetaker — captures interviews without visible meeting bot","Automatic ATS integration with real-time field + note + attachment population","AI-generated branded candidate submittals with video snippets","Multi-language transcription with speaker attribution","Custom-template instant summaries","VoIP calling from inside ATS (browser + mobile)","SOC 2 Type II + GDPR compliance","40+ ATS integrations","In-person + remote meeting capture","Client + candidate calls from one workspace"}', '{"Bullhorn","Vincere","Crelate","Loxo","Zoom","Microsoft Teams","Google Meet","Google Calendar","Outlook","Calendly","WhatsApp"}', true, '{"Recruitment agencies (Bullhorn / Vincere / Crelate / Loxo shops) automating submittals","Agency recruiters needing botless capture for candidate-comfort reasons","Multi-language agency operations (transcription + speaker attribution)","Recruiters spending 8+ hours/week on note-writing + ATS data entry"}', '{"In-house corporate recruiting teams (BrightHire / Metaview fit better)","Assessment-first hiring workflows (HireVue / Modern Hire are purpose-built)","Async video-interview-only workflows (Hireflix is the right tool)","Buyers wanting transparent public pricing before sales call"}', 'The agency-recruiter-specific AI assistant in 2026 — CoRecruit''s botless capture and Bullhorn / Vincere / Crelate / Loxo native ATS integrations make it the natural pick for staffing-firm workflows that BrightHire and Metaview (in-house-focused) don''t serve well. The auto-generated submittals are genuinely time-saving. It''s weaker than BrightHire on in-house recruiting depth, weaker than Eightfold on broader talent-intelligence story, and the no-public-pricing motion is friction. Pick CoRecruit when you''re a recruitment agency on Bullhorn or Vincere; skip if you''re an in-house TA team on Greenhouse or Lever.', now())

